This monitoring solutions is based on a slightly extended version of "dstat", 
and a few bash scripts. All the code is interpreted python and bash.


INSTALL:
- There is no need to install this program, it can be run locally.
- It is designed to run on linux, with python installed 
- for mysql monitoring assumes python-mysql (mysqldb) package, and a non-privileged 
  access to the mysql server.

RUN:
- configure the variable in "setenv" following inline instructions
- launch . ./setenv   (sets few variables)
- launch ./monitor.sh 

